
  <sn><md>### Iron and Aluminium Oxides

Iron and aluminium oxides are known as `sesqui`oxide clays. They accumulate due to `loss of silica and aluminium` through leaching, and they form `under intensive weathering` in warm humid climates. Common examples include **gibbsite (Al₂O₃·3H₂O)** and its hydrated form **Al(OH)₃**, as well as **goethite (Fe₂O₃·3H₂O)** and its hydrated form **FeOOH**. Their presence is responsible for the [red]{.fg-red} and [yellow]{.fg-yellow} colours of highly weathered soils.

